2 Perform the assessment

Reading in all the pairwise intersect data

res <- mclapply(dir(".",pattern=".*-70p-recip\\.tsv"),read.delim,
                stringsAsFactors=FALSE,header=FALSE,mc.cores=6L)

names(res) <- sub("-70p-recip\\.tsv","",dir(".",pattern=".*-70p-recip\\.tsv"))

Create a list of edges

edges.list <- lapply(res,"[",c(9,18))
edges.list <- lapply(edges.list,function(edges){
  cbind(sub(";.*","",sub(".*Name=","",edges[,1])),
        gsub(".*Name=|\\.0$","",edges[,2]))})

Report on the number of links and the number of missing

stats <- do.call(rbind,lapply(edges.list,function(edges){
  tab <- table(table(edges[,2]))
  mult <- rep(as.integer(names(tab[-c(1,length(tab))])),tab[-c(1,length(tab))])
  c(total=nrow(edges),
    gene=length(unique(edges[,1])),
    gene.mapped=length(unique(edges[,2]))-1,
    gene.unique.mapped=sum(table(edges[,2])==1),
    gene.multi=sum(table(edges[,2])>1) - 1,
    gene.multi.mean=mean(mult),
    gene.multi.median=median(mult),
    gene.multi.sd=sd(mult),
    gene.multi.min=min(mult),
    gene.multi.max=max(mult),
    gene.missed=sum(edges[,2]==".")
    )
}))

Graph the edges list

edges.graf <- lapply(lapply(edges.list,function(edges){edges[edges[,2]!=".",]}),
                      graph.edgelist,directed=FALSE)

Get their stats

graf.stats <- do.call(rbind,lapply(edges.graf,function(graf){
  cl <- clusters(graf)
  c(clusters=cl$no,
    singleton=sum(cl$csize==2),
    multiple=length(cl$csize[cl$csize>2]),
    mean=mean(cl$csize[cl$csize>2]-1),
    median=median(cl$csize[cl$csize>2]-1),
    sd=sd(cl$csize[cl$csize>2]-1),
    min=min(cl$csize[cl$csize>2]-1),
    max=max(cl$csize[cl$csize>2]-1))
}))

Draw some examples

The one with the max vertices

baron <- induced.subgraph(graf,get.vertex.attribute(graf,"name")[which(clusters(graf)$membership == which.max(clusters(graf)$csize))])

plot.igraph(baron,vertex.label=NA,edge.arrow.mode=0)

plot.igraph(baron,vertex.label=NA,edge.arrow.mode=0,layout=layout.kamada.kawai(baron))

plot.igraph(baron,vertex.label=NA,edge.arrow.mode=0,layout=layout.sphere(baron))

plot.igraph(baron,vertex.label=NA,edge.arrow.mode=0,layout=layout.spring(baron))

plot.igraph(baron,vertex.label=NA,edge.arrow.mode=0,layout=layout.svd(baron))

This all looks good, lets count the number of clusters and how many species are involved in each

cluster.members.mat <- do.call(rbind,lapply(lapply(lapply(split(get.vertex.attribute(graph = graf,name="name"),
                                         clusters(graf)$membership),substr,1,5),
                            factor,levels=c("Potra","Potri","Potrs")),table))
